1
00:00:01,168 --> 00:00:03,170
♪

2
00:00:05,806 --> 00:00:07,441
Polnareff: Hmm?

3
00:00:07,474 --> 00:00:10,811
Barber: You did say under
the chin, right, polnareff?

4
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:12,145
Polnareff: What the hell?!

5
00:00:12,179 --> 00:00:13,213
( Barber slurps )

6
00:00:13,247 --> 00:00:14,849
Remember me, you fool?

7
00:00:14,882 --> 00:00:17,318
I’m the Anubis stand
you fought earlier.

8
00:00:17,351 --> 00:00:18,552
( Polnareff gasps )

9
00:00:21,722 --> 00:00:24,158
Merde! What do I do now?

10
00:00:24,191 --> 00:00:26,927
Barber: Goodbye! I’m gonna
shave your jaw clean off!

11
00:00:28,228 --> 00:00:31,364
( Screams )

12
00:00:31,398 --> 00:00:32,699
Jotaro: Hmm?

13
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,568
Polnareff: Who--who the hell
are you, really?!

14
00:00:34,601 --> 00:00:37,771
And what have you done
with the barber?!

15
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:39,806
♪

16
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:46,513
Wait. Could it possibly be that
the sword is actually the stand?

17
00:00:46,547 --> 00:00:48,516
Could it be controlling
the barber?

18
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:52,520
So the guy at kom ombo
wasn’t a real stand user!

19
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:53,854
Barber: Polnareff!

20
00:00:57,591 --> 00:01:00,360
Polnareff: But in the end,
it doesn’t matter.

21
00:01:00,394 --> 00:01:02,196
I’m still
way out of your league, buddy.

22
00:01:02,229 --> 00:01:03,897
( Barber chuckles )

23
00:01:03,931 --> 00:01:06,400
( Polnareff gasps )

24
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:07,834
( Groans )

25
00:01:07,868 --> 00:01:11,338
What?! How are you so strong?!

26
00:01:11,371 --> 00:01:13,940
Barber: If you must know,
I took the Liberty

27
00:01:13,974 --> 00:01:16,743
of learning chariot’s moves
during our last fight.

28
00:01:16,777 --> 00:01:19,480
I won’t lose twice
to the same adversary.

29
00:01:19,513 --> 00:01:21,248
Do you understand me?!

30
00:01:23,984 --> 00:01:25,986
♪

31
00:01:28,021 --> 00:01:30,023
( Singing in Japanese )

32
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:51,378
Joseph: That’s it.
You can do it.

33
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:52,379
( Iggy grunting )

34
00:01:52,412 --> 00:01:53,613
Joseph: Ah, come on!

35
00:01:53,647 --> 00:01:54,948
You can’t give up now.

36
00:01:54,982 --> 00:01:56,317
You’ve almost got it!

37
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:59,653
( Laughs )

38
00:01:59,686 --> 00:02:01,288
Oh?

39
00:02:01,321 --> 00:02:02,589
( Iggy farts )

40
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:04,925
( Joseph groans )

41
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,860
( Avdol sighs )

42
00:02:06,894 --> 00:02:08,929
Polnareff and jotaro,

43
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:11,631
they should have
returned by now.

44
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:13,300
( Polnareff gasping )

45
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:18,438
Jotaro: Polnareff,
what’s going on?

46
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:20,474
The barber’s a stand user?

47
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:22,409
Polnareff: Stay back, jotaro!

48
00:02:22,442 --> 00:02:25,812
Th-the sword is the stand!

49
00:02:25,846 --> 00:02:27,715
Trust me. It’s too dangerous

50
00:02:27,748 --> 00:02:30,884
to try using star platinum’s
bare fists against this blade.

51
00:02:30,918 --> 00:02:33,521
The sword’s sharp enough
to slice through them.

52
00:02:33,554 --> 00:02:35,356
This barber
isn’t the stand user,

53
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:36,423
he’s just a puppet!

54
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:38,358
( Barber laughs )

55
00:02:38,392 --> 00:02:40,027
Polnareff: And that’s
not even the worst part!

56
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:43,597
The stand’s even stronger
than it was before!

57
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:46,066
Bastard!

58
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:47,067
Barber: Whoa, there!

59
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,070
( Blade vibrating )

60
00:02:50,103 --> 00:02:52,072
( Barber laughs )

61
00:02:52,105 --> 00:02:55,008
Too much for you? ( Laughs )

62
00:02:55,042 --> 00:02:57,011
I suppose I should be grateful

63
00:02:57,044 --> 00:02:59,747
you’ve shown me
the limits of your defense.

64
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:02,082
Most kind of you. ( Laughs )

65
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:05,352
Now, then, let’s see
if you have what it takes

66
00:03:05,385 --> 00:03:08,722
to survive my next attack,
shall we, polnareff?

67
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:11,391
( Shrieks )

68
00:03:14,061 --> 00:03:15,095
Jotaro: Polnareff!

69
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:18,498
( Shrieking )

70
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:23,470
Polnareff: His powers keep
increasing with every strike!

71
00:03:23,504 --> 00:03:26,507
I can’t keep parrying forever!

72
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:28,609
Sooner or later,
he’s gonna get me!

73
00:03:28,642 --> 00:03:30,444
( Barber shrieks )

74
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:33,814
- Huh?
- Polnareff: Now!

75
00:03:34,815 --> 00:03:36,450
Take this!

76
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:39,720
How in the...

77
00:03:41,488 --> 00:03:44,391
Barber: In case you
haven’t realized the obvious,

78
00:03:44,424 --> 00:03:46,359
I know all your moves.

79
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,862
It doesn’t matter
who my wielder is.

80
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:52,533
As long as i’ve done battle
with you at least once,

81
00:03:52,566 --> 00:03:53,534
I never, ever,

82
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,036
never, ever, never, ever,

83
00:03:56,069 --> 00:04:01,575
never, ever lose twice!

84
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:06,480
Polnareff: I’m not gonna
win this without my rapier.

85
00:04:06,513 --> 00:04:07,781
( Gasps ) Oh, no!

86
00:04:07,814 --> 00:04:09,649
Jotaro, help me out here!

87
00:04:09,683 --> 00:04:11,919
Jotaro: Star platinum.

88
00:04:11,952 --> 00:04:13,020
Barber: Hmm?

89
00:04:13,053 --> 00:04:15,088
♪

90
00:04:16,456 --> 00:04:17,457
( Yells )

91
00:04:17,491 --> 00:04:18,592
Star platinum: Ora!

92
00:04:20,761 --> 00:04:22,062
Polnareff: Think that
finished him off?

93
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:23,997
Jotaro: No.
That punch was shallow,

94
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:26,867
even though it took
just about everything I had.

95
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,602
- Man: Hey, Khan.
- Jotaro: Shit.

96
00:04:28,635 --> 00:04:30,737
- Man: Are you all right?
- Jotaro: This guy’s strong.

97
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,506
It’s been quite a while now

98
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:34,741
since we’ve seen
a stand like this one.

99
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:36,910
It only relies on strength.

100
00:04:36,944 --> 00:04:38,979
( Bystanders gasp )

101
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:41,047
Khan: Not bad, star platinum.

102
00:04:41,081 --> 00:04:43,517
The rumors of your speed
were true.

103
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:49,523
But now that i’ve seen it,
I can easily defeat it.

104
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:56,763
Man: Hey, Khan,
what’s wrong with you?

105
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:57,765
Polnareff: Stay back!

106
00:04:57,798 --> 00:04:59,066
Your friend is being controlled!

107
00:04:59,099 --> 00:05:01,001
If you don’t wanna
get sliced to ribbons,

108
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:02,135
go back inside, and hide!

109
00:05:02,169 --> 00:05:04,905
( Man yells )

110
00:05:06,907 --> 00:05:09,209
Polnareff:
We’re in major trouble, jotaro.

111
00:05:09,243 --> 00:05:12,880
The more we fight this stand,
the faster it gets,

112
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:15,483
and its next attack

113
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:17,785
will probably be
its fastest and strongest yet.

114
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:19,219
We have to be ready

115
00:05:19,253 --> 00:05:21,255
for whatever this glorified
butter knife throws at us!

116
00:05:24,258 --> 00:05:25,659
( Khan shrieks )

117
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:27,127
Jotaro: Move, polnareff!

118
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,195
I’m the one it’s really after!

119
00:05:29,229 --> 00:05:30,931
Polnareff:
Get out of there, jotaro!

120
00:05:30,964 --> 00:05:32,165
Khan: Die!

121
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:33,467
Star platinum: Ora!

122
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,702
Khan: Ah?!

123
00:05:35,736 --> 00:05:37,738
What? With his bare hands?!

124
00:05:37,771 --> 00:05:40,807
Star platinum: Ora!

125
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,976
♪

126
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:46,514
Khan: Amazing. For him
to take that great of a risk...

127
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:50,017
Now it’s become
abundantly clear.

128
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,653
The true source
of star platinum’s strength

129
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:54,688
isn’t its speed or precision.

130
00:05:54,721 --> 00:05:56,556
It’s jotaro’s nerves of steel

131
00:05:56,590 --> 00:05:58,525
and ability
to make quick decisions.

132
00:05:58,559 --> 00:06:00,528
Yes.

133
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:03,130
Now I know it for sure.

134
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:11,572
( Jotaro panting )

135
00:06:14,308 --> 00:06:15,743
Is he dead?

136
00:06:17,177 --> 00:06:19,079
Polnareff:
Hold on a second, jotaro.

137
00:06:19,112 --> 00:06:20,747
He’s just knocked out!

138
00:06:20,781 --> 00:06:23,083
Whatever you do,
don’t touch that sword.

139
00:06:23,116 --> 00:06:24,851
You snapped it in half,

140
00:06:24,885 --> 00:06:27,087
but the stand’s powers
might still be lingering.

141
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:30,190
It controls anyone
who touches it while unsheathed.

142
00:06:30,224 --> 00:06:33,694
Let’s get the blade back inside
without touching the hilt.

143
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:40,000
( Sighs )

144
00:06:43,136 --> 00:06:44,671
( Sighs ) Now what?

145
00:06:44,705 --> 00:06:47,074
If someone draws it again,
we’re done for.

146
00:06:47,107 --> 00:06:50,210
This damn thing has already
learned all of our abilities.

147
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:53,147
I don’t think we’re gonna get
any second chances.

148
00:06:54,314 --> 00:06:56,016
Jotaro: Why not
toss it into the river

149
00:06:56,049 --> 00:06:57,751
to rust at the bottom
of the nile?

150
00:06:57,784 --> 00:06:59,085
Polnareff: The nile, huh?

151
00:06:59,119 --> 00:07:00,954
That sounds like
a great plan to me.

152
00:07:00,988 --> 00:07:02,656
Officer: Hold it!
This is the police!

153
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:03,924
Polnareff: This is
perfect timing!

154
00:07:03,957 --> 00:07:05,659
This guy needs a hospital!

155
00:07:05,692 --> 00:07:08,094
Officer: I have multiple reports
of a brawl at a barber shop!

156
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:09,696
What are you doing
with that sword?!

157
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:10,931
Polnareff: Huh?

158
00:07:10,964 --> 00:07:12,799
Officer: Hand this weapon over
immediately!

159
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,668
Polnareff:
Hey, stop it, would you?!

160
00:07:14,701 --> 00:07:16,269
Don’t pull it out!

161
00:07:16,303 --> 00:07:17,771
( Both grunting )

162
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:20,140
( Polnareff gasps )

163
00:07:20,174 --> 00:07:21,776
( Anubis laughs )

164
00:07:21,808 --> 00:07:23,810
( Polnareff gasping )

165
00:07:26,947 --> 00:07:28,148
Jotaro: Polnareff!

166
00:07:28,182 --> 00:07:29,850
♪

167
00:07:29,883 --> 00:07:31,017
No, damn it.

168
00:07:31,051 --> 00:07:32,786
( Polnareff growls )

169
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:36,823
Jotaro: His eyes, that stare...

170
00:07:36,857 --> 00:07:40,694
Polnareff is being controlled
by the sword’s spell.

171
00:07:40,727 --> 00:07:44,631
Officer: Hey, you there!
You drew the sword!

172
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:45,933
( Polnareff chuckles )

173
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:47,668
I drew the sword, did I?

174
00:07:47,701 --> 00:07:50,304
Hmph. Officer, you should really

175
00:07:50,337 --> 00:07:52,306
be more careful
with your accusations,

176
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:55,142
since you call yourself
a servant of the law.

177
00:07:55,175 --> 00:07:57,644
Officer: Take it easy!
What are you doing?

178
00:07:57,678 --> 00:07:59,113
Polnareff: I’m simply attacking

179
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:02,016
the culprit
who unsheathed the sword!

180
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:07,054
Jotaro: I don’t know who you are
or where you’re hiding,

181
00:08:07,087 --> 00:08:10,257
but I think it’s safe to say
polnareff is under your control.

182
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:12,292
Come to think of it,

183
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:14,795
i’ve never had to fight
against polnareff before.

184
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:15,862
Polnareff: Hmm?

185
00:08:15,896 --> 00:08:17,664
Jotaro: And I can’t pull punches

186
00:08:17,698 --> 00:08:19,366
with chariot as an opponent.

187
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,369
If i’m not smart about this,

188
00:08:22,402 --> 00:08:24,838
I could end up
killing polnareff.

189
00:08:24,872 --> 00:08:27,174
( Polnareff chuckles )

190
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:30,877
As I said before, at this point,
i’ve already witnessed

191
00:08:30,911 --> 00:08:33,247
star platinum’s
entire repertoire of moves,

192
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:36,183
and if i’ve done battle
with you once before,

193
00:08:36,216 --> 00:08:40,987
then I will never lose again!

194
00:08:44,758 --> 00:08:46,293
Star platinum: Ora!

195
00:08:48,061 --> 00:08:50,664
- Polnareff: Hey, now.
- ( Jotaro growls )

196
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:52,866
( Polnareff laughing )

197
00:08:57,437 --> 00:08:59,205
- En garde!
- Jotaro: His speed,

198
00:08:59,239 --> 00:09:01,742
- it’s incredible!
- ( Polnareff laughing )

199
00:09:01,775 --> 00:09:04,211
Jotaro: He’s getting
fast enough to outpace me!

200
00:09:04,244 --> 00:09:07,314
I have to find a way
to stop that sword.

201
00:09:08,982 --> 00:09:10,183
I’ll catch it again.

202
00:09:12,986 --> 00:09:14,054
It sped up!

203
00:09:14,087 --> 00:09:15,388
Polnareff: This time...

204
00:09:15,422 --> 00:09:17,391
I’ll take your head!

205
00:09:17,424 --> 00:09:18,725
Polnareff: Wha--

206
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:20,461
star platinum: Ora!

207
00:09:24,464 --> 00:09:28,368
( Jotaro groaning )

208
00:09:28,402 --> 00:09:31,305
His speed and power
are overwhelming.

209
00:09:31,338 --> 00:09:32,806
Without a doubt,

210
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:35,876
this is the fastest stand
i’ve ever faced.

211
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:39,212
At the rate i’m going,
this won’t end well.

212
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:42,316
I have to fight polnareff
with everything i’ve got,

213
00:09:42,349 --> 00:09:43,917
or i’m dead.

214
00:09:44,918 --> 00:09:47,888
( Polnareff laughs )

215
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:49,790
So you head-butted the sword

216
00:09:49,823 --> 00:09:52,326
after you realized
you couldn’t catch my blade.

217
00:09:52,359 --> 00:09:55,996
Honestly I didn’t think you were
capable of something like that.

218
00:09:56,029 --> 00:09:57,831
I almost had you.

219
00:09:57,865 --> 00:09:59,533
But now...

220
00:10:00,934 --> 00:10:03,236
I’ve acquired
that skill as well.

221
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:05,939
- ( Jotaro gasping )
- ( Polnareff chuckles )

222
00:10:05,973 --> 00:10:07,341
Jotaro...

223
00:10:07,374 --> 00:10:09,343
I can tell that you’re thinking

224
00:10:09,376 --> 00:10:13,080
the only way to survive is
to kill your friend, polnareff.

225
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:14,915
( Chuckles )

226
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,349
Even if you wanted to,

227
00:10:16,383 --> 00:10:18,352
it’s naive to think
it’d be that easy.

228
00:10:18,385 --> 00:10:20,454
Take a close look, jotaro.

229
00:10:20,487 --> 00:10:22,456
What i’m about to show you

230
00:10:22,489 --> 00:10:25,959
will put an end to this
once and for all.

231
00:10:25,993 --> 00:10:27,495
So, let’s see...

232
00:10:29,463 --> 00:10:32,833
If you can beat this, jotaro!

233
00:10:32,866 --> 00:10:36,970
Feast your eyes on
the silver chariot and Anubis

234
00:10:37,004 --> 00:10:38,873
two-sword technique!

235
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:47,681
♪

236
00:10:58,425 --> 00:11:00,560
( Silver chariot laughing )

237
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:05,966
( Star platinum yelling )

238
00:11:12,873 --> 00:11:14,908
( Silver chariot shrieks )

239
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:18,879
( Laughing )

240
00:11:21,448 --> 00:11:22,449
Jotaro: Damn it.

241
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:24,384
This extra sword,

242
00:11:24,418 --> 00:11:26,453
coupled with
his accelerating speed,

243
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:30,056
even star platinum
won’t last long.

244
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:31,692
Polnareff: What’s the matter?

245
00:11:31,725 --> 00:11:35,362
Are you feeling
a little tired, jotaro?!

246
00:11:35,395 --> 00:11:36,863
( Silver chariot grunts )

247
00:11:36,897 --> 00:11:39,400
Jotaro: I’ll stop him
before he kills me. Star finger!

248
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,635
Polnareff: Huh?

249
00:11:41,668 --> 00:11:44,838
♪

250
00:11:44,872 --> 00:11:46,073
( Silver chariot laughs )

251
00:11:46,106 --> 00:11:49,443
My right arm is
as light as a feather now.

252
00:11:49,476 --> 00:11:52,045
Polnareff: Interesting.
I guess that was an option.

253
00:11:52,079 --> 00:11:53,581
( Jotaro gasps )

254
00:11:53,614 --> 00:11:55,449
Polnareff: Didn’t see
that coming, did you?!

255
00:11:55,482 --> 00:11:57,451
Round two! Armor release!

256
00:11:57,484 --> 00:12:00,087
( Star platinum yelling )

257
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:05,625
Silver chariot: You fool!
Your ridiculous, "ora, ora,"

258
00:12:05,659 --> 00:12:07,094
is no match for two swords

259
00:12:07,127 --> 00:12:09,796
wielded
by two master swordsmen!

260
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:14,935
( Star platinum yelling )

261
00:12:18,138 --> 00:12:19,973
Silver chariot:
Your stomach is wide open!

262
00:12:20,007 --> 00:12:21,609
( Jotaro groans )

263
00:12:21,642 --> 00:12:24,912
Silver chariot:
I’ve got you now!

264
00:12:26,113 --> 00:12:27,748
- ( Jotaro gags )
- Polnareff: I did it!

265
00:12:27,781 --> 00:12:29,149
I win!

266
00:12:29,183 --> 00:12:32,086
Anubis: Master dio,
i’ve exterminated jotaro!

267
00:12:32,119 --> 00:12:35,422
I, Anubis,
have finally put him down!

268
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:37,724
Victory is mine!

269
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:45,131
( Anubis laughs )

270
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:46,833
Just forget it.

271
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:49,737
You’re not going to be able
to pull out that blade.

272
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:53,140
Give up already! I’m not sure
your tiny brain has realized it,

273
00:12:53,173 --> 00:12:54,808
but i’ve surpassed
star platinum.

274
00:12:54,842 --> 00:12:57,111
And now the final thrust.

275
00:12:57,144 --> 00:12:58,912
( Jotaro gags )

276
00:12:58,946 --> 00:13:01,148
The final thrust?

277
00:13:01,181 --> 00:13:03,183
Anubis: Yes, precisely!

278
00:13:03,217 --> 00:13:06,587
Once I slice open your bowels,
master dio will rejoice!

279
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:08,655
Jotaro: Please, stop this.

280
00:13:08,689 --> 00:13:10,891
Don’t drive the blade
any further.

281
00:13:10,924 --> 00:13:12,859
It--it’ll be murder.

282
00:13:12,893 --> 00:13:16,196
Anubis: Nice try, but you
won’t get any mercy from me!

283
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:19,867
I can’t wait to spill your guts!

284
00:13:21,068 --> 00:13:24,038
( Laughs)

285
00:13:24,071 --> 00:13:28,475
( Jotaro groans )

286
00:13:28,509 --> 00:13:29,744
- ( Yells )
- ( Star platinum yells )

287
00:13:29,776 --> 00:13:31,011
- Ora!
- ( Anubis squeals )

288
00:13:32,246 --> 00:13:34,014
What the devil?!

289
00:13:34,047 --> 00:13:37,017
You’re breaking me!
I have to pull free!

290
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:40,020
No! Stop!

291
00:13:42,723 --> 00:13:44,191
Jotaro: Maybe i’m wrong,

292
00:13:44,224 --> 00:13:47,194
but weren’t you saying
something about slicing me open?

293
00:13:47,227 --> 00:13:49,196
( Anubis gagging )

294
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:52,766
( Screams )

295
00:13:55,869 --> 00:13:57,838
Jotaro: I told you
it’d be murder,

296
00:13:57,871 --> 00:14:01,208
but the murder I was talking
about was yours, friend.

297
00:14:01,241 --> 00:14:03,110
You’re a pretty easy target

298
00:14:03,143 --> 00:14:05,746
when the sword
isn’t moving around.

299
00:14:07,281 --> 00:14:08,983
( Groans )

300
00:14:09,016 --> 00:14:12,019
Damn it, what a pain in the ass.

301
00:14:12,052 --> 00:14:14,254
This was the toughest opponent
i’ve faced.

302
00:14:14,288 --> 00:14:17,491
That last attack took everything
I had in me and then some.

303
00:14:17,524 --> 00:14:19,593
Luckily it was
just enough to defeat him

304
00:14:19,626 --> 00:14:22,629
before he could learn it like
he did the rest of our attacks.

305
00:14:22,663 --> 00:14:24,765
This is new.

306
00:14:24,798 --> 00:14:27,167
I’ve never been so exhausted.

307
00:14:27,201 --> 00:14:28,569
( Groans )

308
00:14:28,602 --> 00:14:33,040
I have to find avdol
and the old man.

309
00:14:33,073 --> 00:14:35,275
( Polnareff groaning )

310
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:40,147
W-what in the world
just happened?

311
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:41,948
( Jotaro panting )

312
00:14:41,982 --> 00:14:43,050
( Polnareff gasps )

313
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:44,618
The sword didn’t possess me

314
00:14:44,651 --> 00:14:47,521
like it did all
the other guys, did it?

315
00:14:47,554 --> 00:14:48,789
Jotaro: Yeah, it did,

316
00:14:48,822 --> 00:14:50,057
but it’s over now.

317
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:52,292
Polnareff: Forgive me.

318
00:14:52,326 --> 00:14:55,696
Jotaro: Just get
the old man and avdol.

319
00:14:55,729 --> 00:14:57,764
I’m too tired to walk.

320
00:14:57,798 --> 00:14:59,767
Boy: Huh?

321
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,002
♪

322
00:15:02,035 --> 00:15:04,104
Wow, it’s so shiny.

323
00:15:12,246 --> 00:15:14,115
♪

324
00:15:14,147 --> 00:15:16,016
( Boy grunts )

325
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:17,784
( Spits )

326
00:15:17,818 --> 00:15:20,654
Anubis: Now i’ve learned
that trick.

327
00:15:20,687 --> 00:15:22,255
My original stand user

328
00:15:22,289 --> 00:15:26,260
was the sword Smith
who forged me 500 years ago.

329
00:15:26,293 --> 00:15:28,662
He may have perished
centuries ago,

330
00:15:28,695 --> 00:15:31,798
but I survive as a stand
with no master.

331
00:15:31,832 --> 00:15:33,667
Master dio liberated me

332
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:36,236
from the gloomy shadows
of a dusty museum.

333
00:15:37,938 --> 00:15:41,775
And speaking of master dio,
his stand,

334
00:15:41,808 --> 00:15:45,078
the world,
is far more powerful than I.

335
00:15:45,112 --> 00:15:48,282
That’s why I pledged
my undying loyalty.

336
00:15:48,315 --> 00:15:53,287
Jotaro, I swear on my life

337
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:56,990
I will murder you!

338
00:15:57,024 --> 00:15:59,827
I know your strength,
your speed.

339
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:03,297
You won’t see it coming
until it’s too late to stop it!

340
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:05,199
I’ll stab you in the back!

341
00:16:06,834 --> 00:16:11,739
Now die, jotaro!

342
00:16:13,307 --> 00:16:15,009
What just happened?!

343
00:16:16,009 --> 00:16:17,978
Son of a--i missed!

344
00:16:18,011 --> 00:16:19,346
I was tripped by a dog?!

345
00:16:19,379 --> 00:16:22,682
Where the hell
did that mutt come from?!

346
00:16:22,716 --> 00:16:25,018
Polnareff: Hey, iggy,
what are you eating?

347
00:16:25,052 --> 00:16:28,022
Wait a second.
Is that a nasty, old sucker?

348
00:16:28,055 --> 00:16:32,126
Eating right off the ground
again, you filthy mutt.

349
00:16:33,727 --> 00:16:35,996
( Anubis screams )

350
00:16:36,029 --> 00:16:39,065
You’ve gotta be kidding!
It’s the nile river!

351
00:16:39,099 --> 00:16:42,035
Aah! No,
this can’t be happening!

352
00:16:42,069 --> 00:16:44,405
What did I do
to deserve this cruel fate?!

353
00:16:44,438 --> 00:16:48,409
If I fall into the river,
i’m done for! I’ll rust away!

354
00:16:48,442 --> 00:16:51,178
Somebody stop me!

355
00:16:51,211 --> 00:16:54,114
Aah! Oh?!

356
00:16:54,147 --> 00:16:56,182
Aha! I’m heading for a wall!

357
00:16:56,216 --> 00:16:57,918
The wall will stop me!

358
00:16:57,951 --> 00:17:00,053
Lucky me!

359
00:17:00,087 --> 00:17:02,323
What the--shit!

360
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:04,825
I was so panicked
about falling into the water

361
00:17:04,858 --> 00:17:06,960
that I accidentally phased
right through the wall!

362
00:17:06,994 --> 00:17:09,063
I’m gonna fall in!

363
00:17:09,096 --> 00:17:11,865
♪

364
00:17:11,899 --> 00:17:13,834
( Gasps ) Yes, it’s a ship!

365
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:14,901
I’m saved!

366
00:17:14,935 --> 00:17:17,037
If I wedge into those planks,

367
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:19,739
that guy’s curiosity
will make him pull me out,

368
00:17:19,773 --> 00:17:22,009
and then i’ll take over
his pathetic mind!

369
00:17:22,042 --> 00:17:25,012
Once i’m safely
back on dry land,

370
00:17:25,045 --> 00:17:28,048
i’ll use his body
to take revenge on jotaro!

371
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:31,785
( Cow bellows )

372
00:17:31,818 --> 00:17:34,087
Anubis: What?!
A cow is onboard?!

373
00:17:34,121 --> 00:17:37,858
Stop thrashing around!
Hey, calm down!

374
00:17:37,891 --> 00:17:39,426
Would you cool it,
you stupid cow?!

375
00:17:41,395 --> 00:17:43,797
I know! I’ll take over
the cow’s mind!

376
00:17:43,831 --> 00:17:45,166
Then it’ll be a cinch--

377
00:17:47,334 --> 00:17:51,038
i’m not gonna make it in time!

378
00:17:51,071 --> 00:17:52,839
Polnareff: Hey, over there!

379
00:17:52,873 --> 00:17:55,109
That cow’s really rockin’
the boat, don’t you think?

380
00:17:55,142 --> 00:17:57,211
Jotaro: Oh, good grief.
Who gives a damn?

381
00:17:57,244 --> 00:18:01,048
Just go and get the old man
and avdol, will you?

382
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:03,050
( Cow bellowing )

383
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:05,085
♪

384
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,388
( Anubis yells )

385
00:18:07,421 --> 00:18:12,059
Help me!

386
00:18:15,429 --> 00:18:17,064
( Sobs )

387
00:18:18,866 --> 00:18:20,735
Hey! Yoo-hoo!

388
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,769
Oh, fishies, look down here!

389
00:18:23,804 --> 00:18:26,440
Come on. Swim over to me!

390
00:18:26,473 --> 00:18:29,042
Hey, wait! Where are you going?

391
00:18:30,377 --> 00:18:33,080
Hey, Mr. Crab,
it’s a pleasure to meet you.

392
00:18:33,113 --> 00:18:36,316
Would you mind doing me a favor
and taking me ashore?

393
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:38,252
I’ll give you something yummy.

394
00:18:38,285 --> 00:18:41,255
Wait, Mr. Crab!
You just can’t leave me here!

395
00:18:41,288 --> 00:18:43,791
I’ll be rusted through
in a couple of days.

396
00:18:43,824 --> 00:18:45,225
Please, help me.

397
00:18:46,493 --> 00:18:50,464
Don’t leave me here!

398
00:18:50,497 --> 00:18:52,165
( Sobs )

399
00:18:52,199 --> 00:18:54,535
I’m so alone!

400
00:19:00,274 --> 00:19:02,276
♪

401
00:19:09,183 --> 00:19:10,151
Polnareff: Stupid mutt.

402
00:19:10,184 --> 00:19:12,053
What are you staring at?

403
00:19:12,085 --> 00:19:15,155
There’s nothing to eat
over there, flea bag.

404
00:19:15,189 --> 00:19:16,357
( Grunts, groans )

405
00:19:16,390 --> 00:19:18,292
( Iggy farts )

406
00:19:18,325 --> 00:19:19,793
( Laughs )

407
00:19:19,827 --> 00:19:21,162
Polnareff: Why,
you stinkin’ little...

408
00:19:21,195 --> 00:19:22,797
( Gags ) Merde!

409
00:19:22,830 --> 00:19:25,299
What the hell
have you been eating?!

410
00:19:25,332 --> 00:19:27,167
Joseph: Come on, polnareff.

411
00:19:27,201 --> 00:19:29,804
To think all of that happened
without us.

412
00:19:29,837 --> 00:19:31,572
Joseph: You fought
the Anubis stand, huh?

413
00:19:31,605 --> 00:19:34,041
That must have
been rough, jotaro.

414
00:19:34,074 --> 00:19:35,576
Jotaro: Yeah, was.

415
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:37,478
( Polnareff yelling )

416
00:19:37,511 --> 00:19:40,547
Jotaro: That’s the last time
I ever go anywhere with him.

417
00:19:40,581 --> 00:19:42,550
( Both grunt )

418
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:45,152
Joseph: Stop it already,
you stupid mutt!

419
00:19:45,185 --> 00:19:48,789
- Get the hell off my face!
- ( Iggy snarling )

420
00:19:52,793 --> 00:19:54,795
♪

421
00:19:57,798 --> 00:20:01,068
Narrator: The average tourist
to Egypt is mostly unaware

422
00:20:01,101 --> 00:20:03,537
of the country’s
rich ethnic diversity.

423
00:20:04,671 --> 00:20:07,174
For example,
take this Egyptian man

424
00:20:07,207 --> 00:20:09,843
wearing
the traditional jellabiya

425
00:20:09,877 --> 00:20:12,413
or this Egyptian nubian,

426
00:20:12,446 --> 00:20:16,750
and here is a bedouin
from egypt’s desert region.

427
00:20:16,783 --> 00:20:19,185
This gentleman hails from India.

428
00:20:20,487 --> 00:20:22,522
And as a random example,

429
00:20:22,556 --> 00:20:24,324
here’s another Egyptian citizen.

430
00:20:24,358 --> 00:20:26,727
♪

431
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:29,429
Man: Hey! That fox has
got some smokin’-hot legs

432
00:20:29,463 --> 00:20:31,298
that are out of this world.

433
00:20:32,499 --> 00:20:34,568
Boy: I can’t keep
my eyes off her.

434
00:20:34,601 --> 00:20:39,539
Wow! Those puppies’ll
pull you right in, you know.

435
00:20:39,573 --> 00:20:41,642
( Both sigh )

436
00:20:46,813 --> 00:20:48,815
♪

